FitData.layout_name: Intel(R) MeteorLake S and ArrowLake S Chipsets - Corporate - SPI

BuildOutputFilename.label: Output Path
BuildOutputFilename.help_text: Name of the output binary file. In case of multiple binaries, their names will be exactly as the name of the first binary with a suffix number, for example: image.bin (1st binary) ,image1.bin, image2.bin etc.

NumberOfImageSubdivisions.label: Number of Image Subdivisions
NumberOfImageSubdivisions.help_text: Number of output binaries. In case of multiple binaries, their names will be exactly as the name of the first binary with a suffix number, for example: image.bin (1st binary) ,image1.bin, image2.bin etc.

ImageSubdivisionsSizes.label: Image Subdivisions Sizes
ImageSubdivisionsSizes.help_text: Size of each output binary, the values should be separated by ',' (comma). For example if Number of Image Subdivisions is 2 then a possible value would be '32,8'. Use NA to build without size restriction and set NumberOfImageSubdivisions to 1.

RegionOrder.label: Region Order
RegionOrder.help_text: 1=BiosRegion, 2=CseRegion, 3=GbeRegion, 4=PdrRegion, 5=EcRegion, 6=EseRbRegion It is important to note that there is an additional region called the Padding region where all unused space in the IFWI is stored. The region resides either before BIOS's default location or at the end of the IFWI if BIOS's location is changed by the user.

IfwiBuildVersion.label: Ifwi Image Version
IfwiBuildVersion.help_text: 32-bit value to use as the IFWI build version number

DescriptorHashCalc.label: Descriptor Hash calculation
DescriptorHashCalc.help_text: Enabling this feature will allow MFIT and FPT tools to calculate and set descriptor hash. Hash is required when SPI descriptor resiliency is enabled on platform. Disabling this setting will result in skipping the descriptor hash calculation process

DescSigningKey.label: Descriptor Debug Signing Key
DescSigningKey.help_text: This is the path to the private debug key used to sign the Descriptor, while public key hash of it is included in the OEM hash manifest. This setting is operative only when Flash Descriptor Verification is enabled (See DescConfiguration/FdvEnabled).

OemBinary.label: OEM Section Binary
OemBinary.help_text: This loads the OEM Section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

HarnessProject.value: MTP-S A0 PCH (w/ ARL-S + MTL-S CPU) RDL v1.0.0.9 SMIP Change
HarnessProject.label: Harness Project

SelectedRvp.help_text: specify platform RVP for getting Soft Straps default values. supported rvps: HFPGA,ARL-S Hx SODIMM 2DPC (MTP-S + ARL-S),ARL-S SBGA SODIMM 1DPC (MTP-S + ARL-S),MTL-S SODIMM 1DPC (MTP-S + MTL-S),MTL-S UDIMM 1DPC (MTP-S + MTL-S),MTL-S UDIMM 1DPC OC ( MTP-S + MTL-S),MTL-S UDIMM 2DPC (MTP-S + MTL-S),Simics,SLE

InputFile.help_text: This loads the BIOS binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel (R) FIT tool.

MeRegionFile.help_text: This loads the Intel(R) ME binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

PmcBinary.label: PMC Binary File
PmcBinary.help_text: This loads the PMC binary that will be merged into the output image generated by Intel(R) FIT tool.

OEM_CSI_Version.label: OEM Chipset Initialization Package Identifier
OEM_CSI_Version.help_text: Identifies the target product family, platform and stepping of the OEM Chipset Initialization Package.

OEM_CSI_Build_Version.label: OEM Chipset Initialization Package Build Number
OEM_CSI_Build_Version.help_text: Build number to use for the OEM Chipset Initialization Package. The build number must be any whole number from 0 to 65535.

SOC_CSI_Version.label: OEM SOC Chipset Initialization Version
SOC_CSI_Version.help_text: This displays the current System On Chip Chipset Initialization version container in the currently loaded Intel(R) ME binary..

IOE_CSI_Version.label: OEM IOE Chipset Initialization Version
IOE_CSI_Version.help_text: This displays the current IO Expander Chipset Initialization version container in the currently loaded Intel(R) ME binary..

PCH_CSI_Version.label: OEM PCH Chipset Initialization Version
PCH_CSI_Version.help_text: This displays the current IO Expander Chipset Initialization version container in the currently loaded Intel(R) ME binary..

DataResiliency.label: Data Resiliency
DataResiliency.help_text: Enable data restore to manufacturing defaults

ResizeNftpForFtpr.label: Enables NFTP resize for FTPR loading
ResizeNftpForFtpr.help_text: Used to enable NFTP resize for FTPR loading to perform FWU process. Disable for SKU's and platforms with limited image size, without FWU support only.

IfwiCodeResiliencyEnabled.label: Code Resiliency Enabled
IfwiCodeResiliencyEnabled.help_text: Enable Code Resiliency support for critical layout components

EcRegionPointer.label: EC Region Pointer File
EcRegionPointer.help_text: This loads a binary containing the 16 byte value to be written in the Embedded Controller Pointer region.

InputFile.label: EC Binary File
InputFile.help_text: This loads the Embedded Controller binary used for eSPI that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel (R) FIT tool.

Enabled.label: EC Region Enable
Enabled.help_text: This option allows the user to enable or disable the Embedded Controller Data Region.

InputFile.label: GbE Binary File
InputFile.help_text: This loads the Intel(R) Integrated LAN binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel (R) FIT tool.

Enabled.label: GbE Region Enable
Enabled.help_text: This option allows the user to enable or disable the GbE Region

InputFile.label: PDR Binary File
InputFile.help_text: This loads the Platform Data region binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel (R) FIT tool.

Enabled.label: PDR Region Enable
Enabled.help_text: This option allows the user to enable or disable the Platform Data Region.

InputFile.label: PCH Configuration File
InputFile.help_text: This loads the PCH Configuration binary that will be merged into the output image generated by Intel(R) FIT tool.

InputFile.label: SOC Configuration File
InputFile.help_text: This loads the SOC Configuration binary that will be merged into the output image generated by Intel(R) FIT tool.

InputFile.label: ACE Binary File
InputFile.help_text: This loads the ACE binary that will be merged into the output image generated by Intel(R) FIT tool.

ESEBinary.label: SSE Section Binary
ESEBinary.help_text: This loads the Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

num_of_instance_DMUBinary_path.label: Number Of Inputs
num_of_instance_DMUBinary_path.help_text: Number of requested instances to add to image

DMUBinary.label: DMU Section Binary
DMUBinary.help_text: This loads the DMU Section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

num_of_instance_PUNITBinary_path.label: Number Of Inputs
num_of_instance_PUNITBinary_path.help_text: Number of requested instances to add to image

PUNITBinary.label: PUNIT Section Binary
PUNITBinary.help_text: This loads the PUNIT Section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

AUNITBinary.label: AUNIT Section Binary
AUNITBinary.help_text: This loads the AUNIT Section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool. AUNIT is required for ARL only

SocEseSubPartition.label: SOC Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine Sub-Partition

SocEseBinary.label: SOC SSE Section Binary
SocEseBinary.help_text: This loads the SOC Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

SocSphyBinary.label: SOC SPHY Section Binary
SocSphyBinary.help_text: This loads the SOC SPHY Section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

SocPmcBinary.label: SOC PMC Section Binary
SocPmcBinary.help_text: This loads the SOC PMC Section binary that will be merged into the output image generated by the Intel(R) FIT tool.

PchSpiResHldDelay.label: PCH SPI Resume Hold-off Delay
PchSpiResHldDelay.help_text: Specifies the time after the completion of a pri_op before the flash controller sends the resume instruction. If a new pri_op is eligible to be issued prior to the end of this delay time then the pri_op is issued and the timer is reinitialized to tRHD. 3-bit field encodes count with range 0-7. tRHD = count * 2us.

PchSpiSusResEn.label: PCH SPI Suspend / Resume Enabled
PchSpiSusResEn.help_text: When this setting is enabled writes and erases may be suspended to allow a read to be issued on the flash device. When this setting is disabled no transaction will be allowed to the busy flash device.

PchSpiOooEnable.label: PCH SPI Out of Order operation Enabled
PchSpiOooEnable.help_text: When this setting is enabled priority operations may be issued while waiting for write / erase operations to complete on the flash device. When this setting is disabled all write / erase type operations in order.

PchSpiMxWrErResSusInt.label: PCH SPI Max write / erase Resume to Suspend intervals
PchSpiMxWrErResSusInt.help_text: This setting specifies the maximum value for the write and erase Resume to Suspend intervals.

PchSpiIdlDpdwntimeout.label: PCH SPI Idle to Deep Power Down Timeout
PchSpiIdlDpdwntimeout.help_text: SPI Idle to Deep Power Down Timeout Default Specifies the time in microseconds that the Flash Controller waits after all activity is idle before commanding the flash devices to Deep Power down, time = 2^N microseconds.

PchSpiGblProtRng.label: PCH SPI Global Protected Range
PchSpiGblProtRng.help_text: Sets the default value of the Global Protected Range register in the SPI Flash Controller.

SoftReBindEnable.label: Software Re-Binding Enabled
SoftReBindEnable.help_text: When enabled this settings will allow for SPI re-binding to a new PCH during manufacturing and remanufacturing flows prior to platform EOM. Note: Re-binding to a replacement PCH can only be done a maximum of 5 times before the SPI part needs to be re-flashed.

SocSpiResHldDelay.label: SoC SPI Resume Hold-off Delay
SocSpiResHldDelay.help_text: Specifies the time after the completion of a pri_op before the flash controller sends the resume instruction. If a new pri_op is eligible to be issued prior to the end of this delay time then the pri_op is issued and the timer is reinitialized to tRHD. 3-bit field encodes count with range 0-7. tRHD = count * 2us.

SocSpiSusResEn.label: SoC SPI Suspend / Resume Enabled
SocSpiSusResEn.help_text: When this setting is enabled writes and erases may be suspended to allow a read to be issued on the flash device. When this setting is disabled no transaction will be allowed to the busy flash device.

SocSpiOooEnable.label: SoC SPI Out of Order operation Enabled
SocSpiOooEnable.help_text: When this setting is enabled priority operations may be issued while waiting for write / erase operations to complete on the flash device. When this setting is disabled all write / erase type operations in order.

SocSpiMxWrErResSusInt.label: SoC SPI Max write / erase Resume to Suspend intervals
SocSpiMxWrErResSusInt.help_text: This setting specifies the maximum value for the write and erase Resume to Suspend intervals.

SocSpiIdlDpdwntimeout.label: SoC SPI Idle to Deep Power Down Timeout
SocSpiIdlDpdwntimeout.help_text: SPI Idle to Deep Power Down Timeout Default Specifies the time in microseconds that the Flash Controller waits after all activity is idle before commanding the flash devices to Deep Power down, time = 2^N microseconds.

SocSpiGblProtRng.label: SoC SPI Global Protected Range
SocSpiGblProtRng.help_text: Sets the default value of the Global Protected Range register in the SPI Flash Controller.

HostCpuWriteAccessIntelRecommended.label: Host CPU / BIOS Write Access Intel Recommended
HostCpuWriteAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines write access control for the Host CPU / BIOS. For further details on Region Access Control see the Alder Lake SPI Programming Guide.

HostCpuWriteAccessCustom.label: Host CPU / BIOS Write Access Custom
HostCpuWriteAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines Host CPU / BIOS write access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see the SPI Programming guide.

HostCpuReadAccessIntelRecommended.label: Host CPU / BIOS Read Access Intel Recommended
HostCpuReadAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines read access control for the Host CPU / BIOS. For further details on Region Access Control see the Alder Lake SPI Programming Guide.

HostCpuReadAccessCustom.label: Host CPU / BIOS Read Access Custom
HostCpuReadAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines Host CPU / BIOS read access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see the SPI Programming guide.

MeWriteAccessIntelRecommended.label: Intel(R) ME Write Access Intel Recommended
MeWriteAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines write access control for the ME region. For further details on Region Access Control see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

MeWriteAccessCustom.label: Intel(R) ME Write Access Custom
MeWriteAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines ME write access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see SPI Programming guide.

MeReadAccessIntelRecommended.label: Intel(R) ME Read Access Intel Recommended
MeReadAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines read access control for the ME region. For further details on Region Access Control see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

MeReadAccessCustom.label: Intel(R) ME Read Access Custom
MeReadAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines ME read access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see SPI Programming guide.

GbeWriteAccessIntelRecommended.label: GbE Write Access Intel Recommended
GbeWriteAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines write access control for the GBE region. For further details on Region Access Control see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

GbeWriteAccessCustom.label: GbE Write Access Custom
GbeWriteAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines GBE region write access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see SPI Programming guide.

GbeReadAccessIntelRecommended.label: GbE Read Access Intel Recommended
GbeReadAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines read access control for the GBE region. For further details on Region Access Control see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

GbeReadAccessCustom.label: GbE Read Access Custom
GbeReadAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines GBE region read access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see SPI Programming guide.

EcWriteAccessIntelRecommended.label: Embedded Controller Write Access Intel Recommended
EcWriteAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines write access control for the Embedded Controller region. For further details on Region Access Control see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

EcWriteAccessCustom.label: Embedded Controller Write Access Custom
EcWriteAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines Embedded Controller region write access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see SPI Programming guide.

EcReadAccessIntelRecommended.label: Embedded Controller Read Access Intel Recommended
EcReadAccessIntelRecommended.help_text: This setting determines read access control for the Embedded Controller region. For further details on Region Access Control see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

EcReadAccessCustom.label: Embedded Controller Read Access Custom
EcReadAccessCustom.help_text: This setting determines Embedded Controller region read access to the other regions. Note: If pre-locking is not set, closemnf will revert back master access settings to 'golden master access settings'. For further details on Region Access Control see SPI Programming guide.

SpiDualOutReadEnable.label: Dual Output Read Enable
SpiDualOutReadEnable.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Dual Output Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP. If parameter table is not detected via the SFDP, this bit has no effect and Dual Output Read is controlled via the Flash Descriptor Component Section.Dual Output Fast Read Support bit.

SpiDualIoReadEnable.label: Dual I/O Read Enable
SpiDualIoReadEnable.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Dual I/O Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

QuadOutReadEnable.label: Quad Output Read Enable
QuadOutReadEnable.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Quad Output Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

QuadIoReadEnable.label: Quad I/O Read Enable
QuadIoReadEnable.help_text: This soft-strap only has effect if Quad I/O Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

FastReadSupport.label: Fast Read Supported
FastReadSupport.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable support for Fast Read capabilities for flash components. See SPI and SMIP Programming guide further details. Note: This setting needs to be enabled when using Dual / Quad enabled components.

FastReadClockFreq.label: Fast Read Clock Frequency
FastReadClockFreq.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure the flash component clock frequency setting for Fast Read. See SPI and SMIP Programming guide further details.

WriteEraseClockFreq.label: Write and Erase Clock Frequency
WriteEraseClockFreq.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure the flash component clock frequency setting for Write and Erase. See SPI and SMIP Programming guide further details.

ReadIdAndReadStatClkFreq.label: Read ID and Read Status Clock Frequency
ReadIdAndReadStatClkFreq.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure the flash component clock frequency setting for Read ID and Read Status. See SPI and SMIP Programming guide further details.

InvalidInstruction0.label: Invalid Instruction 0
InvalidInstruction0.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction1.label: Invalid Instruction 1
InvalidInstruction1.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction2.label: Invalid Instruction 2
InvalidInstruction2.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction3.label: Invalid Instruction 3
InvalidInstruction3.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction4.label: Invalid Instruction 4
InvalidInstruction4.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction5.label: Invalid Instruction 5
InvalidInstruction5.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction6.label: Invalid Instruction 6
InvalidInstruction6.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

InvalidInstruction7.label: Invalid Instruction 7
InvalidInstruction7.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure invalid instruction to protect against Chip Erase. Note: This setting should be set to '0' if there are not Invalid instructions.

PchTopSwapOverride.label: PCH Top Swap Block Size
PchTopSwapOverride.help_text: This configures the Top Swap Block size for the platform. For further details see Alder Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SocTopSwapOverride.label: SoC Top Swap Block Size
SocTopSwapOverride.help_text: This configures the Top Swap Block size for the platform. For further details see Alder Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

BiosRedAssistance.label: BIOS Redundancy Assistance
BiosRedAssistance.help_text: In case of BIOS boot failure, CSME will configure the platform to boot with backup BIOS using Top Swap. Note: This option is only available when Boot Guard is enabled.

HwBindingEn.label: Hardware Binding Enabled
HwBindingEn.help_text: This setting configures the FPF Hardware and RPMC / RPMB binding behavior for the platform image. If this setting is enabled FPF Hardware and RPMC / RPMB binding behavior will occur when platform close manufacturing flow is executed with Intel(R) FPT. If this setting is disabled FPF Hardware and RPMC / RPMB binding behavior will not take place when close manufacturing flow is executed. Note: For Revenue parts this setting will be ignored and FPF Hardware and RPMC / RPMB binding behavior will take place when close manufacturing flow is executed.

RpmcSupported.label: RPMC FW Supported
RpmcSupported.help_text: This setting determines if RPMC is enabled. Note: The SPI parts being used need to support RPMC In order to use this feature.

RpmcOverEc.label: RPMC Over EC Supported
RpmcOverEc.help_text: This setting determines if RPMC is enabled over eSPI OOB to be handled by EC (EC might provide RPMC capabilities or offload it to another SPI flash device).

RpmcRebindEn.label: RPMC Rebinding Supported
RpmcRebindEn.help_text: This setting determines if Rebinding of RPMC enabled SPI parts is enabled.

ProcMissingDetect.label: Missing Processor Detection Alert
ProcMissingDetect.help_text: This setting determines if missing processor detection is enabled on Desktop / Workstation platforms. Note: This feature will only work if the platform has the appropriate glue logic present.

HideMEBxFwUpdCtrl.label: Hide MEBx Firmware Update Control
HideMEBxFwUpdCtrl.help_text: This setting allows customers to hide the Firmware Update option in the MEBx interface.

FwUpdateOemId.label: Firmware Update OEM ID
FwUpdateOemId.help_text: This setting allows configuration of an OEM unique ID to ensure that customers can only update their platform with images from the OEM of the platform.

OemFwVersion.label: OEM FW Version
OemFwVersion.help_text: This setting contains the OEM IP version

HmrfpoEnable.label: Intel(R) ME Region Flash Protection Override
HmrfpoEnable.help_text: This setting enables descriptor unlock of the ME Region when the HMRFPO message is sent to firmware prior to BIOS End of POST.

OemTag.label: OEM Tag
OemTag.help_text: This is a free form 32bit field that allows the OEM to configure their own unique identifier in the firmware image.

FwAutoBist.label: Automatic Built in Self Test
FwAutoBist.help_text: This setting enables the firmware Automatic Built in Self Test which is executed during first platform boot after initial image flashing.

FlexibleEomSettings.value_list: ['Lock Descriptor and OEM Configs', 'Lock OEM Configs Only', 'Lock Descriptor Only', 'Do not lock Descriptor and OEM Configs']
FlexibleEomSettings.label: Flexible EOM setting options
FlexibleEomSettings.help_text: This setting deteremines which settings will be automatically commited during End of Manufacturing flows. Note: The FPFs, RPMB / RPMC and set manufacturing mode settings are mandatory and cannot be overridden revenue parts. Simulation can be done on non-revenue part with the Hardware binding set to disabled.

EomFirstBootEnabled.label: EOM on First Boot Enabled
EomFirstBootEnabled.help_text: This setting determines if End of Manufacturing will be triggered on first boot of the platform after flashing. Note: When this setting is enabled Intel(R) CSME will enter End of Manufacturing regardless of the descriptor settings.

PrtcBackupPower.label: Persistent PRTC Backup Power
PrtcBackupPower.help_text: FPF that indicates if the device is designed such that it may lose PRTC power more than 10 times throughout the normal lifecycle of the product and hence has no persistent time or AR protection. At EOM, this value is burned to an FPF, and can never be changed.

MeMeasuredBootState.label: Intel(R) ME Measured Boot State
MeMeasuredBootState.help_text: When measured boot is enabled firmware will use additional extended registers for all IUPs and Key Manifests that firmware loads and verifies from flash. Note: When measured boot is enabled any IUPs or firmware updates will require a global reset

ECOOBSmbusAddr.label: eSPI OOB EC SMBUs Address
ECOOBSmbusAddr.help_text: This setting determines the SMBUS address for eSPI OOB to be handled by EC.

AmtSupported.label: Intel(R) AMT Supported
AmtSupported.help_text: This setting allows customers to disable Intel(R) AMT on the platform. Note: Either Intel(R) AMT or Intel(R) ISM can be enabled as manageability application

ISMSupported.label: Intel(R) Standard Manageability
ISMSupported.help_text: Intel(R) Standard Manageability is a manageability mode that supports a subset of the Intel(R) Active Management Technology (Intel(R) AMT). Note: Either Intel(R) AMT or Intel(R) ISM can be enabled as manageability application

MngAppPowerUpState.label: Manageability Application initial power-up state
MngAppPowerUpState.help_text: This setting allows customers to determine the power up state for Intel(R) AMT or Standard Manageability. Note: If this setting is disabled Intel(R) AMT or Standard Manageability can still be re-enabled through the MEBx interface.

AmtIdleTimeout.label: Idle Timeout
AmtIdleTimeout.help_text: This setting configures the idle timeout value before Manageability app enters into an off state.

AmtWdAutoReset.label: Watchdog Automatic Reset Enabled
AmtWdAutoReset.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable the Intel (R) ME firmware to trigger an automatic platform reset if either the MEI or Agent Presence are in a hung state. Note: This feature only allows one reset at a time when the watchdog expires. After this feature has triggered a reset it must be re-armed for re-use via management console.

MngHwStatus.label: Manageability Application HW State
MngHwStatus.help_text: This setting will permanently disable Manageability hardware through platform FPFs. At End-of-Manufacturing (EOM), enable/disable policy value is committed to FPF and can never be changed. Permanently disabling Manageability HW via this setting requires 'Manageability Application Supported' is set to permanently disabled and 'Intel(R) ME Network Services Supported' is set to disabled. Note: When 'Manageability Application Hardware Status' is Enabled but 'Manageability Application Supported' is set to permanently disabled and 'Intel(R) ME Network Services Supported' is set to disabled, Manageability HW is disabled by a soft strap.

KvmSupported.label: KVM Redirection Supported
KvmSupported.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable the KVM Redirection capabilities of the firmware. Note: If this setting have been set to disabled it cannot be re-enabled once the descriptor has been locked.

KvmScreenBlnkEnable.label: Firmware KVM Screen Blanking
KvmScreenBlnkEnable.help_text: This setting enables KVM Screen blanking capabilities in the firmware image. Note: This feature is dependent on processor level support.

PkiDomainSuffix.label: PKI Domain Name Suffix
PkiDomainSuffix.help_text: This setting allows OEMs to pre-configure the Domain Name Suffix used for PKI provisioning in their firmware image. Note: For normal out-of- box provisioning functionality this setting should be left empty.

CertActive.label: Certificate Enabled
CertActive.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 1.

CertFriendly.label: Certificate Friendly Name
CertFriendly.help_text: This setting allows customers to assign a user friendly name for PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 1. Maximum of 32 characters.

CertStream.label: Certificate Stream
CertStream.help_text: This setting allows customers to input hash stream for PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 1. If enabled the certificate will be used in addition those already preloaded in base firmware during provisioning. Note: If the platform is un-configured the Custom Certificate Hash will be deleted.

CertActive.label: Certificate Enabled
CertActive.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 2.

CertFriendly.label: Certificate Friendly Name
CertFriendly.help_text: This setting allows customers to assign a user friendly name for PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 2. Maximum of 32 characters.

CertStream.label: Certificate Stream
CertStream.help_text: This setting allows customers to input hash stream for PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 1. If enabled the certificate will be used in addition those already preloaded in base firmware during provisioning. Note: If the platform is un-configured the Custom Certificate Hash will be deleted.

CertActive.label: Certificate Enabled
CertActive.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 3.

CertFriendly.label: Certificate Friendly Name
CertFriendly.help_text: This setting allows customers to assign a user friendly name for PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 3. Maximum of 32 characters.

CertStream.label: Certificate Stream
CertStream.help_text: This setting allows customers to input hash stream for PKI provisioning Custom Certificate 1. If enabled the certificate will be used in addition those already preloaded in base firmware during provisioning. Note: If the platform is un-configured the Custom Certificate Hash will be deleted.

CertActive.label: Certificate Enabled
CertActive.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable PKI provisioning Default certificate 1.

CertFriendly.label: Certificate Friendly Name

RedirectionPrivSecLevel.label: Redirection Privacy / Security Level
RedirectionPrivSecLevel.help_text: This setting allows customers to configure the Privacy and Security level for redirection operations. Default enables all redirection ports (User consent is configurable). Enhanced enables all redirection ports (User consent is required and cannot be disabled). Extreme disables all redirection capabilities.

RedirectionLanguage.label: Redirection Localized Language
RedirectionLanguage.help_text: this setting allows customers to configure which localized language will be used initially by firmware for user consent output information (examples: may be displayed before sol / kvm session starts)

TlsCryptoSupport.label: Transport Layer Security Crypto Support
TlsCryptoSupport.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable firmware Transport Layer Security support. Note: If this is disabled TLS will be permanently disabled in the firmware image.

OCRSupported.label: Intel(R) One Click Recovery supported
OCRSupported.help_text: This setting enables the One Click Recovery capability

RPESupported.label: Intel(R) Remote Platform Erase supported
RPESupported.help_text: This setting enables the Remote Platform Erase capability

Hdcp5kedisp1.label: HDCP Internal Display Port 1 - 5K
Hdcp5kedisp1.help_text: This setting determines which port is connected to internal display 1

Hdcp5kedisp2.label: HDCP Internal Display Port 2 - 5K
Hdcp5kedisp2.help_text: This setting determines which port is connected to internal display 2

PlatformIntegrity.label: Hash Key Configuration for Bootguard / ISH

SkipOemKeysCheck.label: Skip OEM Keys Check
SkipOemKeysCheck.help_text: This is meant for debugging purposes only. Enabling this parameter impacts image creation procedure in FIT tool only.

OemExtInputFile.label: OEM Key Manifest Binary
OemExtInputFile.help_text: Signed manifest file containing hashes of keys used for signing components of image. This setting is only configurable when OEM signing is enabled (See Hash Key Configuration for Bootguard/ISH/OemPublicKeyHash).

OemPublicKeyHash.label: 1st OEM Public Key Hash
OemPublicKeyHash.help_text: Raw hash string for the SHA-384 hash of the OEM public key corresponding to the private key used to sign the OEM Key hash manifest. When manufacture is completed, this hash value is burned into an FPF, and is permament. This value is used to verify the OEM Key hash, and also DnX images. OEM signing is disabled when this hash is set to all 0s.

OemKeyRevEnable.label: OEM Key Revocation Supported
OemKeyRevEnable.help_text: Enabling the OEM key revocation mechanism requires 'OEM Public Key Hash' and 'Second OEM key hash' to be configured.

excludeMasterAccess.label: Exclude master access in the signature
excludeMasterAccess.help_text: include/exclude master access in the signature.

Range1Offset.label: Range 1 offset
Range1Offset.help_text: Range 1 offset covers manifest, cannot be changed

Range1Size.label: Range 1 size
Range1Size.help_text: Range 1 size covers manifest, cannot be changed

Range2Offset.label: Range 2 offset
Range2Offset.help_text: Range 2 offset covers master access offset

Range2Size.label: Range 2 size
Range2Size.help_text: Range 2 size covers master access size

Range3Offset.label: Range 3 offset
Range3Offset.help_text: Range 3 offset covers OEM defined unprotected range start

Range3Size.label: Range 3 size
Range3Size.help_text: Range 3 size covers OEM defined unprotected range length

Range4Offset.label: Range 4 offset
Range4Offset.help_text: Range 4 offset covers OEM defined unprotected range start

Range4Size.label: Range 4 size
Range4Size.help_text: Range 4 size covers OEM defined unprotected range length

Range5Offset.label: Range 5 offset
Range5Offset.help_text: Range 5 offset covers OEM defined unprotected range start

Range5Size.label: Range 5 size
Range5Size.help_text: Range 5 size covers OEM defined unprotected range length

Range6Offset.label: Range 6 offset
Range6Offset.help_text: Range 6 offset covers OEM defined unprotected range start

Range6Size.label: Range 6 size
Range6Size.help_text: Range 6 size covers OEM defined unprotected range length

Range7Offset.label: Range 7 offset
Range7Offset.help_text: Range 7 offset covers OEM defined unprotected range start

Range7Size.label: Range 7 size
Range7Size.help_text: Range 7 size covers OEM defined unprotected range length

Range8Offset.label: Range 8 offset
Range8Offset.help_text: Range 8 offset covers OEM defined unprotected range start

Range8Size.label: Range 8 size
Range8Size.help_text: Range 8 size covers OEM defined unprotected range length

BtGuardKeyManifestId.label: Key Manifest ID
BtGuardKeyManifestId.help_text: ODM identifier used during the Key manifest authentication process. This setting is only configurable, and must be non-0, when OEM Public Key Hash is set (See PlatformIntegrity/OemPublicKeyHash).

BtGuardProfileConfig.value_list: ['Boot Guard Disabled', 'Debug Profile', 'Verified Boot', 'Verified and Measured Boot']
BtGuardProfileConfig.label: Boot Guard Profile
BtGuardProfileConfig.help_text: This option configures the which boot guard policy profile will be used. Note: all profiles with the exception of profile 0 - fvme support txt being enabled.

BtGuardBspInitEnable.label: BSP Initialization
BtGuardBspInitEnable.help_text: This setting determines BSP behavior when it receives an INIT signal. When set to 'Enabled' BSP will behave normally if it receives an INIT (Disabled BSP Initialization (DBI) bit = 0). When set to 'Disabled' BSP will shutdown if it receives an INIT ('DBI' bit = 1).

BtGuardCpuDebugEnable.label: CPU Debugging
BtGuardCpuDebugEnable.help_text: This setting determines if CPU debug modes will be displayed. When set to 'Yes' CPU debugging is enabled.

PttSupported.label: Intel(R) PTT Supported
PttSupported.help_text: This setting permanently disables Intel(R) PTT in the firmware image.

PttPwrUpState.label: Intel(R) PTT initial power-up state
PttPwrUpState.help_text: This setting determines if Intel(R) PTT is enabled on platform power-up.

PttSupportedFpf.label: Intel(R) PTT Supported [FPF]
PttSupportedFpf.help_text: This setting will permanently disable Intel(R) PTT through platform FPFs. Caution: Using this option will permanently disable Intel(R) PTT on the platform hardware.

SpiOverTpmBusEnable.label: TPM Over SPI Bus Enabled
SpiOverTpmBusEnable.help_text: This setting determines the clock frequency setting to be used for the TPM over SPI bus.

PchSpiOverTpmClkFreq.label: PCH TPM Clock Frequency
PchSpiOverTpmClkFreq.help_text: This setting determines the clock frequency setting to be used for the TPM over SPI bus.

SocSpiOverTpmClkFreq.label: SoC TPM Clock Frequency
SocSpiOverTpmClkFreq.help_text: This setting determines the clock frequency setting to be used for the TPM over SPI bus.

BiosGrdProtOvrdEn.label: BIOS Guard Protection Override Enabled
BiosGrdProtOvrdEn.help_text: This setting allows BIOS Guard to bypass SPI flash controller protections (i.e. Protected Range Registers and Top Swap).

TxtSupported.label: TXT Supported
TxtSupported.help_text: This setting determines is enabled for the platform.

CryptoHwSupport.label: Crypto HW Support
CryptoHwSupport.help_text: This setting can be used to disable crypto funtionality. This settings disables all crypto dependent features.

IntelFpfFirmwareVersionControlConfigurat.label: Intel(R) FPF Intel(R) Firmware Version Control (Intel(R) FVC) Configuration

GscSvnEnabled.label: GSC HW SVN Enabled
GscSvnEnabled.help_text: Configure usage of Intel FPF for Intel(R) Firmware Version Control (Intel(R) FVC) mechanism for GSC FW Manifest component.

FidoSupported.label: Fast identity online device onboarding state
FidoSupported.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable the Fast identity online device onboarding (FIDO) state of the firmware.

DisableJTAGAndDisableBSCAN.label: Disable JTAG
DisableJTAGAndDisableBSCAN.help_text: When this setting is enabled, JTAG access will be disabled, when manufacture is completed. An Intel DPT token can be used to re-enable JTAG.

DisableBoundaryScan.label: Disable Boundary Scan
DisableBoundaryScan.help_text: When this setting is enabled, BSCAN access will be disabled, when manufacture is completed. An Intel DPT token can be used to re-enable BSCAN.

vproNicEnabled.label: Platform vPro 2.5 Wired LAN State
vproNicEnabled.help_text: YES = Discrete NIC enabled in platform NO = Integrated GBE LAN enabled in platform

vproNicSMBusAddress.label: Platform vPro 2.5G Wired LAN SMBUS slave address
vproNicSMBusAddress.help_text: Platform discrete NIC slave address Note: Input needs to be in HEX format(OEM specific), e.g. 0x12

vproDockEnabled.label: vPro Over Thunderbolt Dock State
vproDockEnabled.help_text: YES = Enables communication with, vPro supporting NIC, via TBT dock NO = No support for vPro dock solution

TypeCPortRetimerMCTPSmbusAddr.label: vPro 2.5G Wired LAN on dock slave SMBUS Address
TypeCPortRetimerMCTPSmbusAddr.help_text: Dock NIC slave address Note: Input needs to be in HEX format(OEM specific), e.g. 0x12

ThunderboltPort1SMBUSAddress.label: Thunderbolt Port1 SMBUS Address
ThunderboltPort1SMBUSAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address. Note: Input needs to be in HEX format(OEM specific), e.g. 0x12

ThunderboltPort2SMBUSAddress.label: Thunderbolt Port2 SMBUS Address
ThunderboltPort2SMBUSAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address. Note: Input needs to be in HEX format(OEM specific), e.g. 0x12

ThunderboltPort3SMBUSAddress.label: Thunderbolt Port3 SMBUS Address
ThunderboltPort3SMBUSAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address. Note: Input needs to be in HEX format(OEM specific), e.g. 0x12

ThunderboltPort4SMBUSAddress.label: Thunderbolt Port4 SMBUS Address
ThunderboltPort4SMBUSAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address. Note: Input needs to be in HEX format(OEM specific), e.g. 0x12

LanEnable.label: Intel(R) Integrated Wired LAN Enabled
LanEnable.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable Intel(R) Integrated LAN operation over the PCIe Port selected by the GbE PCIe Port Select option.

LanPhyPwrCtrlGpd11Config.label: LAN PHY Power Control GPD11 Signal Configuration
LanPhyPwrCtrlGpd11Config.help_text: This setting allows the user to assign the LAN PHY Power Control signal to GbE or as GDP11. Note: If using Intel(R) Integrated LAN this setting should be set to ""Enable as LANPHYPC"".

GbeMacSmbAddrs.label: GbE MAC SMBus Address
GbeMacSmbAddrs.help_text: This setting configures Intel(R) Integrated Wired LAN MAC SMBus address to accept SMBus cycles from the PHY. Note: Recommended setting is 70h.

GbeMacSmbAddrsEn.label: GbE MAC SMBus Address Enabled
GbeMacSmbAddrsEn.help_text: This enables the Intel(R) Integrated Wired LAN MAC SMBus address. Note: This setting must be enabled if using Intel(R) Integrated LAN.

GbePHYSmbAddrs.label: GbE PHY SMBus Address
GbePHYSmbAddrs.help_text: This is the Intel PHY SMBus address. This field must be programmed to 64h. GbE PHY SMBus Address and GbE MAC address have to be programmed to 64h and 70h in order to ensure proper arbitration of SMBus communication between the Intel integrated MAC and PHY.

PhyConnected.value_list: ['No PHY Connected', 'PHY on SMBus', 'PHY on SMLink0', 'PHY on SMLink1']
PhyConnected.label: PHY Connection
PhyConnected.help_text: This selects which SMBus network is used to connect GbE PHY to MAC/PCH.

MELanPowerWell.label: LAN Power Well
MELanPowerWell.help_text: This setting allows the customer to configure the powerwell that will be used by Intel(R) Integrated LAN. Note: Recommended setting is SLP_LAN#.

LanPhyPwrUpTime.label: LAN PHY Power Up Time
LanPhyPwrUpTime.help_text: This bit determines how long the delay for LAN PHY to power up after de-assertion of SLP_LAN#

SlpWlanGdp9Config.label: SLP_WLAN# / GDP9 Signal Configuration
SlpWlanGdp9Config.help_text: This setting allows user the to assign the WLAN Power Control signal to WLAN or as GDP9. Note: If using Intel(R) Wireless LAN this setting should be set to ""Enable as SLP_WLAN#"".

MEWlanPowerWell.label: WLAN Power Well
MEWlanPowerWell.help_text: This setting allow the customer to configure the powerwell that will be used by Intel(R) wireless lan. note: recommended setting is slp_wlan#

MeClinkEnable.label: Intel(R) ME CLINK Signal Enabled
MeClinkEnable.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable the Wireless LAN CLINK signal through Intel(R) ME firmware. Note: For using Intel(R) vPro Wireless solutions this should be set to Yes.

WlanUcode.label: WLAN Microcode
WlanUcode.help_text: This setting allows OEMs to configure which Intel(R) Wireless LAN card microcode to load into the firmware image.

TsnEnabled.label: Time Sensitive Networking
TsnEnabled.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable Time Sensitive Networking on the platform.

BUFF_EN_SRC1.label: SRCCLKREQ#[1]
BUFF_EN_SRC1.help_text: Enable/Disable the SOC SRCCLKREQ1# buffer. For a mapped SRCCLKREQ1# this must be set to 'Enable' in order to enable the associated mapped CLKOUT_S_Gen5_P/N output buffer

BUFF_EN_SRC2.help_text: Enable/Disable the SOC SRCCLKREQ2# buffer. For a mapped SRCCLKREQ2# this must be set to 'Enable' in order to enable the associated mapped CLKOUT_S_Gen5_P/N output buffer

SRC_MUXSEL_CFG1.help_text: Set the SOC CLKOUT_S_GEN5_P1/N1 to SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only SRCCLKREQ[3:1]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_S_GEN5_P1/N1

SRC_MUXSEL_CFG2.label: CLKOUT_S_GEN5_P2/N2 to SRCCLKREQ#

SSC_en.label: CLKOUT_S_GEN5_P/N[3:1] SSC
SSC_en.help_text: Enable/Disable SSC for the SOC CLKOUT_S_GEN5_P/N[3:1] clocks

EXT_INJ_BCLK.label: EXT_INJ_BCLK_P/N
EXT_INJ_BCLK.help_text: Set external or internal clock mode for the 100 MHz Differential bus clock input to the processor

EXT_INJ_PHYREFCLK.label: EXT_INJ_PHYREF_P/N
EXT_INJ_PHYREFCLK.help_text: Set external or internal clock mode for the 100 MHz Differential bus clock input for PCIe and DMI Overclocking

IOE_BUFF_EN_SRC0.label: I_SRCCLKREQ0#
IOE_BUFF_EN_SRC0.help_text: Enable/Disable the IOE I_SRCCLKREQ0# buffer. For a mapped I_SRCCLKREQ0# this must be set to 'Enable' in order to enable the associated mapped CLKOUT_I_Gen[5:4]_P/N output buffer

IOE_BUFF_EN_SRC1.label: I_SRCCLKREQ1#
IOE_BUFF_EN_SRC1.help_text: Enable/Disable the IOE I_SRCCLKREQ1# buffer. For a mapped I_SRCCLKREQ1# this must be set to 'Enable' in order to enable the associated mapped CLKOUT_I_Gen[5:4]_P/N output buffer

IOE_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG0.help_text: Set the IOE CLKOUT_I_GEN5_P0/N0 to I_SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only I_SRCCLKREQ[1:0]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_I_GEN5_P0/N0

IOE_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG1.label: CLKOUT_I_GEN4_P1/N1 to I_SRCCLKREQ#
IOE_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG1.help_text: Set the IOE CLKOUT_I_GEN4_P1/N1 to I_SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only I_SRCCLKREQ[1:0]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_I_GEN4_P1/N1

IOE_SSC_en.help_text: Enable/Disable SSC for the IOE CLKOUT_I_GEN[5:4]_P/N[1:0] clocks

PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG10.help_text: Set the PCH CLKOUT_PCIE_P10/N10 to SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only SRCCLKREQ[13:0]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_PCIE_P10/N10

PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG11.label: CLKOUT_PCIE_P11/N11 to SRCCLKREQ#
PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG11.help_text: Set the PCH CLKOUT_PCIE_P11/N11 to SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only SRCCLKREQ[13:0]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_PCIE_P11/N11

PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG12.label: CLKOUT_PCIE_P12/N12 to SRCCLKREQ#
PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG12.help_text: Set the PCH CLKOUT_PCIE_P12/N12 to SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only SRCCLKREQ[13:0]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_PCIE_P12/N12

PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG13.label: CLKOUT_PCIE_P13/N13 to SRCCLKREQ#
PCH_SRC_MUXSEL_CFG13.help_text: Set the PCH CLKOUT_PCIE_P13/N13 to SRCCLKREQ# Mapping. Only SRCCLKREQ[13:0]# can be mapped to CLKOUT_PCIE_P13/N13

PCH_SSC_en.label: CLKOUT_S_GEN5_P/N[3:1] SSC
PCH_SSC_en.help_text: Enable/Disable SSC for the PCH CLKOUT_PCIE_P/N[13:0] clocks

PCH_EXT_INJ_PHYREFCLK.label: EXT_INJ_PHYREF_P/N
PCH_EXT_INJ_PHYREFCLK.help_text: Set external or internal clock mode for the PCH differential clock input used for DMI overclocking

tPch45TimingConfig.label: PCH clock output stable to PROCPWRGD high (tPCH45)
tPch45TimingConfig.help_text: This setting configures the minimum timing from XCK_PLL locked to CPUPWRGD high. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

tPch46TimingConfig.label: PROCPWRGD and SYS_PWROK high to SUS_STAT# de-assertion (tPCH46)
tPch46TimingConfig.help_text: This setting configures the minimum timing from CPUPWRGD assertion to SUS_STAT#. For further details see Meteor Lake Controller Hub EDS.

OcWdtSsEnable.value_list: ['OC WDT Disabled', 'OC WDT 3 Second Timeout', 'OC WDT 5 Second Timeout', 'OC WDT 10 Second Timeout', 'OC WDT 15 Second Timeout', 'OC WDT 30 Second Timeout', 'OC WDT 45 Second Timeout', 'OC WDT 60 Second Timeout']
OcWdtSsEnable.label: Over Clocking Watchdog Self Start Enable
OcWdtSsEnable.help_text: This setting affect whether the Over Clocking Watchdog Timer is enabled to automatically start on Host power cycle.

ApwrokTiming.label: APWROK Timing
ApwrokTiming.help_text: This soft strap determines the timing between the SLP_A# pin de-asserting and the APWROK timer expiration.

tPch33TimerEnable.label: PCIe Power Stable Timer (tPCH33)
tPch33TimerEnable.help_text: This setting configures the enables / disables the tPCH33 timer. When enabled PCH will count 99ms from PWROK assertion before PLTRST# is de-asserted. Note: The recommended setting is ""Disabled""

SmbAlrtModeConfig.value_list: ['Enable as GPP_C2', 'Enable as Intel(R) SMBus ASD']
SmbAlrtModeConfig.label: Intel(R) SMBus ASD Mode Configuration
SmbAlrtModeConfig.help_text: This setting determines the native mode of operation for the Intel(R) SMBus ASD signal.

SMBusTcoSlaveSelect.label: SMBus / SMLink TCO Slave Connection
SMBusTcoSlaveSelect.help_text: This setting configures the TCO Slave connection to ether the Intel(R) SMBus or SMLink0. For further details see Alder Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SMBusI2cAddress.label: Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address
SMBusI2cAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address. Note: This setting is only used for testing purposes. The recommended setting is ""0000000""

SMBusAsdAddress.label: Intel(R) SMBus ASD Address
SMBusAsdAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus Alert Sending Device Address. For details see Meteor Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

SMBusI2cEnable.label: Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address Enabled
SMBusI2cEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables the Intel(R) SMBus I2C Address. Note: This setting is only used for testing purposes. The recommended setting is ""No""

SMBusAsdEnable.label: Intel(R) SMBus ASD Address Enabled
SMBusAsdEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables the Intel(R) SMBus Alert Sending Device. For details see Meteor Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

SMBusAsfId.label: Intel(R) SMBus Subsystem Vendor & Device ID for ASF
SMBusAsfId.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus Subsystem Vendor and Device ID for ASF. For details see Alder Lake SPI Programming guide further details.

SLink0Enable.label: SMLink0 Enabled
SLink0Enable.help_text: This setting enables / disables SMLink0 interface. For further details see Alder Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS. Note: If using Intel(R) NFC this setting must be set to ""Yes"".

SLink0I2cAddress.label: SMLink0 I2C Address
SLink0I2cAddress.help_text: This setting configures the SMLink0 I2C Address. Note: This setting is used as a part of the Intel(R) vPro Thunderbolt(tm) dock configuration.

SLink0MctpAddress.label: Intel(R) SMLink0 MCTP Address
SLink0MctpAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMLink0 MCTP Address.

SMLink0I2cEnable.label: SMLink0 I2C Address Enabled
SMLink0I2cEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables the SMLink0 I2C Address. Note: This setting is used as a part of the Intel(R) vPro Thunderbolt(tm) dock configuration.

SLink0MctpEnable.label: Intel(R) SMLink0 MCTP Address Enabled
SLink0MctpEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables the Intel(R) SMLink0 MCTP Address.

SLink0freq.label: SMLink0 Frequency
SLink0freq.help_text: This setting determines the frequency at which the SMLink0 will operate. Note: The recommended setting is ""1MHz""

SLink1Enable.label: SMLink1 Enabled
SLink1Enable.help_text: This setting enables / disables SMLink1 interface. For further details see Alder Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS. Note: This setting must be set to "Yes" if using PCH / MCP Thermal reporting.

SLink1GPTargetEnable.label: SMLink1 GP Target Address Enabled
SLink1GPTargetEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables SMLink1 GP Target Address interface. For further details see Alder Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS. Note: This setting must be set to ""Yes"" if using PCH / MCP Thermal reporting.

SLink1GPTargetAddress.label: SMLink1 GP Target Address
SLink1GPTargetAddress.help_text: This setting configures SMLink1 GP Target Address. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SLink1I2cAddress.label: SMLink1 I2C Target Address
SLink1I2cAddress.help_text: This setting configures SMLink1 I2C Target Address. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SLink1MctpAddress.label: SMLink1 MCTP Address
SLink1MctpAddress.help_text: This setting configures the Intel(R) SMBus MCTP Address. Note: This setting is only used for testing purposes. The default setting is ""0000000""

SLink1I2cEnable.label: SMLink1 I2C Target Address Enabled
SLink1I2cEnable.help_text: This setting configures SMLink1 I2C Target Address. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SLink1MctpEnable.label: SMLink1 MCTP Address Enabled
SLink1MctpEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables the Intel(R) SMBus MCTP Address. Note: This setting is only used for testing purposes. The recommended setting is ""No""

SLink1freq.label: SMLink1 Frequency
SLink1freq.help_text: This setting determines the frequency at which the SMLink1 will operate. Note: The recommended setting is ""100KHz""

PchEspiEcBusfreq.label: PCH eSPI / EC Bus Frequency
PchEspiEcBusfreq.help_text: Indicates the maximum frequency of the eSPI bus that is supported by the eSPI Master and platform configuration (trace length, number of Slaves, etc.). The actual frequency of the eSPI bus will be the minimum of this field and the Slave's maximum frequency advertised in its General Capabilities register.

PchEspiEcCrcCheckEnable.label: PCH eSPI / EC CRC Check Enabled
PchEspiEcCrcCheckEnable.help_text: This setting enables CRC checking on eSPI Slave 0 channel.

PchEspiEcMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Dual', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
PchEspiEcMaxIoMode.label: PCH eSPI / EC Maximum I/O Mode
PchEspiEcMaxIoMode.help_text: Indicates the maximum IO Mode (Single/Dual/Quad) of the eSPI bus that is supported by the eSPI Master and specific platform configuration. The actual IO Mode of the eSPI bus will be the minimum of this field and the Slave's maximum IO Mode advertised in its General Capabilities register.

PchEspiEcSlave1DeviceEn.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device Enabled
PchEspiEcSlave1DeviceEn.help_text: This setting enables the Slave device on the eSPI interface.

PchEspiEcSlv1DevBusfreq.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device Bus Frequency
PchEspiEcSlv1DevBusfreq.help_text: This setting configures the maximum operating frequency of the Slave device.

PchEspiEcSlv1DevMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Duel', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
PchEspiEcSlv1DevMaxIoMode.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device Maximum I/O Mode
PchEspiEcSlv1DevMaxIoMode.help_text: This setting configures the maximum I/O mode of the Slave device.

PchEspiEcSlve1CrcChkEn.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device CRC Check Enabled
PchEspiEcSlve1CrcChkEn.help_text: This setting determines if CRC checking is enabled on the eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device channel.

PchEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshMor.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash Multiple Outstanding Requests Enable
PchEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshMor.help_text: This setting enabled multiple outstanding requests for the eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash device.

PchEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshOoo.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash Channel OOO Enable
PchEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshOoo.help_text: This setting enables Out or Order requests on the eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash device.

PchEspiEcMaxOutReqMstrFlCh.label: PCH eSPI / EC Max Outstanding Request for Master Attached Flash Channel
PchEspiEcMaxOutReqMstrFlCh.help_text: This setting determines the Maximum outstanding requests on the eSPI / EC Master Attached Flash Channel.

PchEspiEcSlave2DeviceEn.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device Enabled
PchEspiEcSlave2DeviceEn.help_text: This setting enables the Slave device on the eSPI interface.

PchEspiEcSlve2CrcChkEn.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device CRC Check Enable
PchEspiEcSlve2CrcChkEn.help_text: This setting determines if CRC checking is enabled on the eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device channel.

PchEspiEcSlv2DevMaxIoMode.value_list: ['PCH Single', 'Single and Duel', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
PchEspiEcSlv2DevMaxIoMode.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device Maximum I/O Mode
PchEspiEcSlv2DevMaxIoMode.help_text: This setting configures the maximum I/O mode of the Slave device.

PchEspiEcSlv2DevBusfreq.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device Bus Frequency
PchEspiEcSlv2DevBusfreq.help_text: This setting configures the maximum operating frequency of the Slave device.

PchEspiEcSlave3DeviceEn.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device Enabled
PchEspiEcSlave3DeviceEn.help_text: This setting enables the Slave device on the eSPI interface.

PchEspiEcSlve3CrcChkEn.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device CRC Check Enable
PchEspiEcSlve3CrcChkEn.help_text: This setting determines if CRC checking is enabled on the eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device channel.

PchEspiEcSlv3DevMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Duel', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
PchEspiEcSlv3DevMaxIoMode.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device Maximum I/O Mode
PchEspiEcSlv3DevMaxIoMode.help_text: This setting configures the maximum I/O mode of the Slave device.

PchEspiEcSlv3DevBusfreq.label: PCH eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device Bus Frequency
PchEspiEcSlv3DevBusfreq.help_text: This setting configures the maximum operating frequency of the Slave device.

SocEspiEcBusfreq.label: SoC eSPI / EC Bus Frequency
SocEspiEcBusfreq.help_text: Indicates the maximum frequency of the eSPI bus that is supported by the eSPI Master and platform configuration (trace length, number of Slaves, etc.). The actual frequency of the eSPI bus will be the minimum of this field and the Slave's maximum frequency advertised in its General Capabilities register.

SocEspiEcCrcCheckEnable.label: SoC eSPI / EC CRC Check Enabled
SocEspiEcCrcCheckEnable.help_text: This setting enables CRC checking on eSPI Slave 0 channel.

SocEspiEcMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Dual', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
SocEspiEcMaxIoMode.label: SoC eSPI / EC Maximum I/O Mode
SocEspiEcMaxIoMode.help_text: Indicates the maximum IO Mode (Single/Dual/Quad) of the eSPI bus that is supported by the eSPI Master and specific platform configuration. The actual IO Mode of the eSPI bus will be the minimum of this field and the Slave's maximum IO Mode advertised in its General Capabilities register.

SocEspiEcSlave1DeviceEn.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device Enabled
SocEspiEcSlave1DeviceEn.help_text: This setting enables the Slave device on the eSPI interface.

SocEspiEcSlv1DevBusfreq.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device Bus Frequency
SocEspiEcSlv1DevBusfreq.help_text: This setting configures the maximum operating frequency of the Slave device.

SocEspiEcSlv1DevMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Duel', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
SocEspiEcSlv1DevMaxIoMode.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device Maximum I/O Mode
SocEspiEcSlv1DevMaxIoMode.help_text: This setting configures the maximum I/O mode of the Slave device.

SocEspiEcSlve1CrcChkEn.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device CRC Check Enable
SocEspiEcSlve1CrcChkEn.help_text: This setting determines if CRC checking is enabled on the eSPI / EC Slave 1 Device channel.

SocEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshMor.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash Multiple Outstanding Requests Enable
SocEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshMor.help_text: This setting enabled multiple outstanding requests for the eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash device.

SocEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshOoo.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash Channel OOO Enable
SocEspiEcSlvAtchdFlshOoo.help_text: This setting enables Out or Order requests on the eSPI / EC Slave Attached Flash device.

SocEspiEcMaxOutReqMstrFlCh.label: SoC eSPI / EC Max Outstanding Request for Master Attached Flash Channel
SocEspiEcMaxOutReqMstrFlCh.help_text: This setting determines the Maximum outstanding requests on the eSPI / EC Master Attached Flash Channel.

SocEspiEcSlave2DeviceEn.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device Enabled
SocEspiEcSlave2DeviceEn.help_text: This setting enables the Slave device on the eSPI interface.

SocEspiEcSlve2CrcChkEn.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device CRC Check Enable
SocEspiEcSlve2CrcChkEn.help_text: This setting determines if CRC checking is enabled on the eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device channel.

SocEspiEcSlv2DevMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Duel', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
SocEspiEcSlv2DevMaxIoMode.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device Maximum I/O Mode
SocEspiEcSlv2DevMaxIoMode.help_text: This setting configures the maximum I/O mode of the Slave device.

SocEspiEcSlv2DevBusfreq.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 2 Device Bus Frequency
SocEspiEcSlv2DevBusfreq.help_text: This setting configures the maximum operating frequency of the Slave device.

SocEspiEcSlave3DeviceEn.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device Enabled
SocEspiEcSlave3DeviceEn.help_text: This setting enables the Slave device on the eSPI interface.

SocEspiEcSlve3CrcChkEn.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device CRC Check Enable
SocEspiEcSlve3CrcChkEn.help_text: This setting determines if CRC checking is enabled on the eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device channel.

SocEspiEcSlv3DevMaxIoMode.value_list: ['Single', 'Single and Duel', 'Single and Quad', 'Single, Dual and Quad']
SocEspiEcSlv3DevMaxIoMode.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device Maximum I/O Mode
SocEspiEcSlv3DevMaxIoMode.help_text: This setting configures the maximum I/O mode of the Slave device.

SocEspiEcSlv3DevBusfreq.label: SoC eSPI / EC Slave 3 Device Bus Frequency
SocEspiEcSlv3DevBusfreq.help_text: This setting configures the maximum operating frequency of the Slave device.

EspiEcRefClkFreqSel.label: eSPI / EC Reference Clock Frequency Select
EspiEcRefClkFreqSel.help_text: This setting determines frequency of the reference clock being used on the eSPI / EC bus.

DmiPciPortStagger.label: DMI / PCIe Port Staggering Enabled
DmiPciPortStagger.help_text: This setting configures DMI and PCIe for Port Staggering. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

DmiLaneReversal.label: DMI Lane Reversal
DmiLaneReversal.help_text: This setting allow the DMI Lane signals to be reversed. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

DmiLaneWidth.label: DMI Lane Width
DmiLaneWidth.help_text: This setting determines the number of DMI lanes available.

DmiAcCoupling.label: DMI AC Coupling Select
DmiAcCoupling.help_text: This setting determines if DMI is operating in AC or DC coupled mode.

SlpS3Gdp4Config.label: SLP_S3# / GPD4 Signal Configuration
SlpS3Gdp4Config.help_text: This setting allows the user to assign the SLP_S3# Power Control signal as SLP_S3# or as GDP4. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SlpS4Gdp5Config.label: SLP_S4# / GPD5 Signal Configuration
SlpS4Gdp5Config.help_text: This setting allows the user to assign the SLP_S4# Power Control signal as SLP_S4# or as GDP5. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SlpAGpd6Config.label: SLP_A# / GPD6 Signal Configuration
SlpAGpd6Config.help_text: This setting allows the user to assign the SLP_A# Power Control signal as SLP_A# or as GDP6. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

SlpS5Gdp10Config.label: SLP_S5# / GPD10 Signal Configuration
SlpS5Gdp10Config.help_text: This setting allows the user to assign the SLP_S5# Power Control signal as SLP_S5# or as GDP10. For further details see Meteor Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS.

DeepSxSupportEnable.label: Deep Sx Enabled
DeepSxSupportEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables support for Deep Sx operation. For further details see Arrow Lake Platform Controller Hub EDS. Note: Support for Deep Sx is board design dependent.

PchThrmlRprtngEn.label: Thermal Power Reporting Enabled
PchThrmlRprtngEn.help_text: When this setting is enabled a once-per-second timer interrupt is sent which triggers firmware to report power and temperature information as reported by configuration registers. Note: When this setting is disabled also ensure that the once-per-second timer interrupt associated with this feature is also disabled.

IshPowerUpState.label: Integrated Sensor Hub Initial Power Up State
IshPowerUpState.help_text: This setting allows customers to determine the power up state for ISH.

IshSupported.label: Integrated Sensor Hub Supported
IshSupported.help_text: This setting allows customers to enable / disable ISH on the platform.

InputFile.label: ISH Input File
InputFile.help_text: Path to your ISH firmware binary file.

Length.label: Integrated Sensor Hub Length
Length.help_text: Total size (in bytes) of the ISH code partition including reserved space. It is recommended to be at least 256kb.

PdtBinary.label: ISH PDT Binary File
PdtBinary.help_text: Path to your PDT binary file.

IdlmFile.label: Intel(R) Debug Loadable Module - IDLM
IdlmFile.help_text: This allows an IDLM binary to be merged into output image built by Intel (R) FIT

DelayedAuthMode.label: Delayed Authentication Mode Enabled
DelayedAuthMode.help_text: This setting enables Delayed Authentication Mode on the platform.

RomTracePchPreBiosEn.value_list: ['Trace Hub Pre-BIOS PCH Disabled', 'Trace Hub Pre-BIOS PCH Enabled']
RomTracePchPreBiosEn.label: Intel(R) Trace Hub PCH Pre-BIOS Trace Enabled
RomTracePchPreBiosEn.help_text: This setting will enable / disable Intel(R) Trace Hub Pre-BIOS Tracing capabilities on the PCH.

RomTraceEmergencyModeEn.label: Intel(R) Trace Hub Emergency Mode Enabled
RomTraceEmergencyModeEn.help_text: When enabled, Intel(R) ME programs Intel(R) Trace Hub to send debug traces over DCI OOB without target configuration from the Intel(R) System Studio tool. Note: This is intended for debug purposes only and should not be used in "the" shipping configuration.

RomTracePreBiosEn.value_list: ['Trace Hub Pre-BIOS Disabled', 'Trace Hub Pre-BIOS Enabled']
RomTracePreBiosEn.label: Intel(R) Trace Hub Pre-BIOS Trace Enabled
RomTracePreBiosEn.help_text: This setting will enable / disable Intel(R) Trace Hub Pre-BIOS Tracing capabilities.

IntelTrcHubBinary.label: Intel(R) Trace Hub Binary
IntelTrcHubBinary.help_text: This is the Intel(R) trace hub configuration file. which will be applied by intel me to configure Intel(R) trace hub. use this option to restore Intel(R) trace hub configuration when necessary.

RomTraceFiltering.label: Intel(R) Trace Hub Filtering
RomTraceFiltering.help_text: This setting allows a user input binary for filtering of output messages for Intel(R) Trace Hub

PmcDbgMsgsEnable.label: PMC Hub Debug Messages Enabled
PmcDbgMsgsEnable.help_text: This setting enables PMC FW trace messages to Intel(R) Trace Hub - When set to Yes, enables trace messages.

MeRstBehavior.value_list: ['Intel(R) ME Alternate image boot', 'Intel(R) ME will Halt']
MeRstBehavior.label: Intel(R) ME Reset Behavior
MeRstBehavior.help_text: This setting determines Intel(R) ME behavior when boot image errors are encountered. Warning: This setting should be used for debug purposes only.

AfsIdleReclaim.label: AFS Idle Flash Reclaim Enabled
AfsIdleReclaim.help_text: This controls enabling / disabling of Intel(R) ME AFS Idle flash reclaim capabilities. Note: This setting should be used for debug purposes only.

DbgOverridePreProdSi.label: Debug Override Pre-Production Silicon
DbgOverridePreProdSi.help_text: Allows the OEM to control FW features to assist with pre-production platform debugging. This control has no effect if used on production silicon. Note: Certain options will do not work when the descriptor is locked (See FW Bring-up Guide for setting details). Important: Due to an HW issue, this setting should be set temporarily to 0x7 to prevent boot issues.

DbgOverrideProdSi.label: Debug Override Production Silicon
DbgOverrideProdSi.help_text: Allows the OEM to control FW features to assist with production platform debugging. Note: Certain options will do not work when the descriptor is locked (See FW Bring-up Guide for setting details).

EseFirmwareDebuggingOverrides.label: Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine Firmware Debugging Overrides

EseRomBpInputFile.label: SSE ROM Bypass
EseRomBpInputFile.help_text: Path to the Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine ROM Bypass binary file. This capability is only supported pre-EOM and must be signed for FIT to integrate it into the final IFWI

ProcEmulation.value_list: ['No Emulation', 'EMULATE Intel (R) vPro (TM) capable Processor', 'EMULATE Intel (R) Core (TM) branded Processor', 'EMULATE Intel (R) Celeron (R) branded Processor', 'EMULATE Intel (R) Pentium (R) branded Processor', 'EMULATE Intel (R) Xeon E (R) branded Processor', 'EMULATE Intel (R) Xeon W (R) Manageability capable Processor']
ProcEmulation.label: Processor Emulation
ProcEmulation.help_text: This setting determines processor type to be emulated on pre-production silicon.

DciDbcEnable.label: Intel(R) DCI DbC Interface Enabled
DciDbcEnable.help_text: This setting enables / disables the Intel (R)DCI DbC interface. NOTE: Applies only before End of Manufacture.

PchEspiEcLowFreqOvrd.label: PCH eSPI / EC Low Frequency Debug Override
PchEspiEcLowFreqOvrd.help_text: When enabled this setting will divide eSPI clock frequency by 8. Note: This setting should only be used for debugging purposes. Leaving this setting enable will impact eSPI performance.

SocEspiEcLowFreqOvrd.label: SoC eSPI / EC Low Frequency Debug Override
SocEspiEcLowFreqOvrd.help_text: When enabled this setting will divide eSPI clock frequency by 8. Note: This setting should only be used for debugging purposes. Leaving this setting enable will impact eSPI performance.

EarlyUsb2DbcOverType-AConfiguration.label: Early USB2 DBC over Type-A Configuration

Usb2DbcPortEn.value_list: ['No USB2 Ports', 'USB2 Port 1', 'USB2 Port 2', 'USB2 Port 3', 'USB2 Port 4', 'USB2 Port 5', 'USB2 Port 6', 'USB2 Port 7', 'USB2 Port 8', 'USB2 Port 9', 'USB2 Port 10', 'USB2 Port 11', 'USB2 Port 12', 'USB2 Port 13', 'USB2 Port 14']
Usb2DbcPortEn.label: USB2 DbC port enable
Usb2DbcPortEn.help_text: This setting dedicates USB2 STD-A port for USB2 DbC exclusively. It blocks functional traffic on this port and USB.DbC traffic on all other ports, including USB Type-C ports. Note: These fields do not apply to USB Type-C ports.

EnEarlyUsb2DbcCon.label: Enable early USB2 DbC connection
EnEarlyUsb2DbcCon.help_text: This setting enables a delay during Intel(R) ME FW bring-up to allow USB2 DbC connection to be established. Note: Early USB2 DBC can only be used on Port 1

SocEseFirmwareDebuggingOverrides.label: SOC Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine Firmware Debugging Overrides

SocEseRomBpInputFile.label: SOC SSE ROM Bypass
SocEseRomBpInputFile.help_text: Path to the SOC Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine ROM Bypass binary file. This capability is only supported pre-EOM and must be signed for FIT to integrate it into the final IFWI

IntelDPTToken.label: Intel DPT Token
IntelDPTToken.help_text:
This allows to enable debug capabilities using Secure Token binary file.
Note: Need to move to separated 'Secure Debug' group.

PchSseFirmwareDebuggingOverrides.label: PCH Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine Firmware Debugging Overrides

PchSseRstBehavior.label: PCH SSE Reset Behavior
PchSseRstBehavior.help_text: This setting determines PCH Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine behavior when boot image errors are encountered. Warning: This setting should be used for debug purposes only.

PchSseAfsIdleReclaim.label: PCH SSE AFS Idle Flash Reclaim Enabled
PchSseAfsIdleReclaim.help_text: This controls enabling / disabling of PCH Intel(R) Silicon Security Engine AFS Idle flash reclaim capabilities. Note: This setting should be used for debug purposes only.

NumActiveBigCore.value_list: ['All Cores Active', '1 Core Active', '2 Cores Active', '3 Cores Active', '4 Cores Active', '5 Cores Active']
NumActiveBigCore.label: Number of Active Big Cores
NumActiveBigCore.help_text: This setting controls the number of active Big Core processors. Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only. See BIOS Spec for more details on enabling / disabling processor cores.

BistInit.label: BIST Initialization
BistInit.help_text: This setting determines if BIST will be run at platform reset after BIOS requested actions. Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only.

FlexRatio.label: Flex Ratio
FlexRatio.help_text: This setting controls the maximum processor non-turbo ratio. Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only. See BIOS Spec for more details on maximum processor non-turbo ratio configuration.

CpuMaxFreqBoot.label: Processor Boot at P1 Frequency
CpuMaxFreqBoot.help_text: This setting determines if the processor will boot at P1 frequency. Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only.

JtagPwrDisable.value: No JTAG Power on C10 and Lower
JtagPwrDisable.value_list: ['No JTAG Power on C10 and Lower', 'JTAG Power on C10 and Lower']
JtagPwrDisable.label: JTAG Power Disable
JtagPwrDisable.help_text: This setting determines if JTAG power will be maintained on C10 or lower power states. Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only.

ActiveComputeSmallCores.value_list: ['All Cores Active', '1 Core Active', '2 Cores Active', '3 Cores Active', '4 Cores Active', '5 Cores Active', '6 Cores Active', '7 Cores Active', '8 Cores Active', '9 Cores Active', '10 Cores Active', '11 Cores Active', '12 Cores Active', '13 Cores Active', '14 Cores Active', '15 Cores Active']
ActiveComputeSmallCores.label: Active Compute Small Cores
ActiveComputeSmallCores.help_text: This setting controls the number of active small core processors. Note: If the Number of Active Big Cores setting is configured to a specific number of individual cores active and the Number of Active Compute Small Cores is configured to All Cores Active the Compute Small core processors will be disabled. Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only. See BIOS Spec for more details on enabling / disabling processor cores.

NumActiveSmallCores.value_list: ['Disable All Cores', '1 Core Active', '2 Cores Active']

Note: This strap is intended for debugging purposed only. See BIOS Spec for more details on enabling / disabling processor cores.

CpuP1BootRatio.label: Processor P1 Boot Ratio

PchI2c0BuffPdStr18v.label: PCH - I2C0 buffer PD strength for 1.8V operation
PchI2c0BuffPdStr18v.help_text: This setting configures the buffer pull-down strength for I2C0_SDA and I2C0_SCL signals (1.8 V operation). Note: When configuring this setting the corresponding PCH - I2C0 buffer PU Strength 1.8V setting must be set to the same value.

PchI2c0BuffPuStr18v.value_list: ['100 Ohms', '66 Ohms', '50 Ohms', '40 Ohms', '33 Ohms', '25 Ohms']
PchI2c0BuffPuStr18v.label: PCH - I2C0 buffer PU strength for 1.8V operation
PchI2c0BuffPuStr18v.help_text: This setting configures the buffer pull-up strength for I2C0_SDA and I2C0_SCL signals (1.8 V operation). Note: When configuring this setting the corresponding PCH - I2C0 buffer PD Strength 1.8V setting must be set to the same value.

PchI2c0CurrentSrcStr.label: PCH - I2C0 current source strength
PchI2c0CurrentSrcStr.help_text: This setting configures the current source strength for I2C0 signals.

PchI2c1BuffPdStr18v.help_text: This setting configures the buffer pull-down strength for I2C1_SDA and I2C1_SCL signals (1.8 V operation). Note: When configuring this setting the corresponding PCH - I2C1 buffer PU Strength 1.8V setting must be set to the same value.
